    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-03-05T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-03-05T09:00:00-05:00" n="552"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d552">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4591: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland (<persName corresp="#p_WHR1"
                            type="from">Wilson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-03-05T15:00:00+01:00"
                            >March 5, 1932—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 5—10:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>55. <persName corresp="#p_YWW1">Yen</persName> sent me a note during the session
                    this morning to the effect that it would be helpful if the American Government
                    would urge, at the various capitals, that the delegates of the separate nations
                    be instructed to adopt a firm attitude in the Assembly on matters of
                    principle.</p>
                <p>Unless you feel that I should adopt a contrary course I propose to tell <persName
                        corresp="#p_YWW1">Yen</persName> that I am making your views very clear to
                    such delegates as I consider useful here in Geneva, that the fact that I am
                    doing this unofficially renders it no less effective and that such action as he
                    proposed might cross wires and would surely be misinterpreted in view of our
                    nonmembership in the League.<note n="52" xml:id="d552fn52">The Secretary of
                        State replied to telegram No. 34, March 7, 8 p.m., “I approve the course
                        proposed.”</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_WHR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
